<div id="review_3065680387" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3065680387" />
    <a title="Michael Esquivel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/92602548-michael-esquivel"><img alt="Michael Esquivel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1580446562p2/92602548.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3065680387?book_show_action=true">Jan 10, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Esquivel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Esquivel" href="/user/show/92602548-michael-esquivel">Michael Esquivel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781539797722" href="/book/show/32823376-a-short-account-of-the-destruction-of-the-indies">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/92602548-michael-esquivel?shelf=mexico">mexico</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/92602548-michael-esquivel?shelf=survival">survival</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3065680387" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8820418760634523745">Friar de Las Casas gave a detailed, eye-witness account as to the atrocities inflicted on the Native people of Latin America by the Spaniards. Many people are aware of some of the travesties these people suffered, but most do not know to what extent. The Spaniards only cared about finding gold by any means necessary. Each chapter describes a different location and each chapter tells the same story: The Spaniards enter a new territory and are greeted by the Native people. The Spaniards demand gol</span>
  <span id="freeText8820418760634523745" style="display:none">Friar de Las Casas gave a detailed, eye-witness account as to the atrocities inflicted on the Native people of Latin America by the Spaniards. Many people are aware of some of the travesties these people suffered, but most do not know to what extent. The Spaniards only cared about finding gold by any means necessary. Each chapter describes a different location and each chapter tells the same story: The Spaniards enter a new territory and are greeted by the Native people. The Spaniards demand gold and torture the chiefs until their people produce the gold. Even when gold is produced, the chiefs are tortured and burned to death anyway because it isn’t enough. Women and babies are tortured, people’s limbs and noses are hacked off, and the Spaniards’ dogs routinely chase and devour innocent people, to name a few abominations. This was a short, but very tough book to get through; tough because of the graphic and detailed descriptions of the many horrors that thousands of Native people endured in their own land.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8820418760634523745" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

